
HOW TO

  1. clone this repo to ~/.bash
	git clone git://github.com/px/bash-settings.git ~/.bash/

	OR to your own Code directory

	git clone git://github.com/px/bash-settings.git ~/tmp/Code/bash-settings/

	cd ~/ ; ln -sf ~/tmp/Code/bash-settings/ .bash


  2. add the following lines into ~/.bash_login for Linux (or .bashrc or Mac):

### Cut #####

## set our system type
mySystem=`uname -s`
## set our local host name (eg. everything before the first period.)
myName=`uname -n | cut -f1 -d.`

if [[ $mySystem == "Darwin" ]]; then
        ## if my ~/.bash/mb-$myName file exists
        [ -f ~/.bash/mb-$myName.sh ] && source ~/.bash/mb-$myName.sh
        [ -f ~/.bash/mbp-$myName.sh ] && source ~/.bash/mbp-$myName.sh
fi
        
if [[ $mySystem  == "Linux" ]]; then
        ## if my ~/.bash/server-$myName file exists
        [ -f ~/.bash/desktop-$myName.sh ] && source ~/.bash/desktop-$myName.sh
        [ -f ~/.bash/server-$myName.sh ] && source ~/.bash/server-$myName.sh

fi

## [ -f ~/.bash/<configuration-name>.sh ] && source ~/.bash/<configuration-name>.sh
### / Cut #####


  3. reload the shell

DIRECTORY STRUCTURE

  /*.sh      # particular configuration (my-server.sh, my-macbook.sh etc.)
  /common    # environment-independant settings and aliases
  /desktop   # settings relevant to desktop computers (GNU/Linux or Mac OSX)
  /server    # settings relevant to servers (mostly Linux-related) 

Files are stored in ÜTF±8 encoding.
